
    Open Source at SCO
    Ron Record
    rr@sco.com

    This session will provide a general overview of Open Source use at SCO.
    Intended as a wide-ranging free-form interactive discussion of Open Source
    issues, the session will include Open Source porting guidelines for SCO 
    developers, a review of Open Source components distributed and supported
    by SCO, tips for finding and integrating Open Source projects in your
    solution stacks, SCO Skunkware issues, and a brief overview of the Open
    Source porting services offered by SCO Professional Services.

    Attendee feedback on issues raised in this session is highly desired
    as future work in this area is driven by customer, reseller and channel
    needs and requirements.

